{% call components.section("Behavior") -%}

    <h4>Trigger</h4>

    <p>A popover requires a <strong>trigger</strong> to be displayed. A trigger can be an icon, text, or another element that encourages a user to interact with it. To close a popover, a user must select the close button, make a selection outside of the popover, or press the <strong>Escape (esc)</strong> key.</p>

    {% call components.example(palette='lightest') %}
      <img src="{{ '/assets/popover/popover-behavior-trigger.svg' | url }}" alt=" Popover component behavior, trigger" style="--inline-img-max-width: 832px;">
    {%- endcall %}

    <h4>Form</h4>

    <p>If you need to place a popover above a form field, you may use an icon as a trigger. However, an icon is not the only visual element that can trigger a popover.</p>

    {% call components.example(palette='lightest') %}
